English name of language   : Norwegian Sign Language

Native name of language (transcribed into ASCII): norsk tegnspra*k

Reference to published description of the language (book or article):

Schroeder, Odd-Inge: Introduction to the history of Norwegian Sign 
Language. In: Fischer, Renate / Lane, Harlan (eds): Looking back. A 
reader on the history of deaf communities and their sign languages. 
(International Studies on Sign Language and Communication of the 
Deaf; 20) Hamburg : Signum (1993) - pp. 231-248

Vogt-Svendsen, Marit: Norwegian Sign Language. In: Cleve, John V. van 
(ed): Gallaudet encyclopedia of deaf people and deafness. Vol. 3. 
S-Z,Index. New York, NY [u.a.] : McGraw-Hill Book Company, Inc. 
(1987) - pp. 95-96

Schroeder, Odd-Inge: Fonologien i Norsk Tegnspra*k. In: Tellevik, Jon 
Magne / Vogt-Svendsen, Marit / Schroeder, Odd-Inge (eds): Tegnspra*k 
og undervisning av do/ve barn: nordisk seminar. Trondheim : Tapir 
(1983)

Askeland, Norunn / et al.: Tegnspra*k som forstespra*k 9. klasse. 
Grunnbok : video med et utvalg tekster fra grunnbok gjengitt pa* 
tegnspra*k. Knyttet til: Norsk i a*ttende. Oslo : Aschehoug 
Undervisning, [s.d.] (Video 112min)
